Calida CEO Sees Prices Rising 10%-15% Next Year, Le Matin Says

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 
2011-02-27T15:17:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/calida-ceo-sees-prices-rising-10-15-next-year-le-matin-says.html
  Calida Holding AG , the Swiss maker
of ski underwear and French lingerie, will raise its prices
between 10 percent and 15 percent next year because of a surge
in the cost of cotton and as its product range evolves, Le Matin
Dimanche said, citing an interview with Chief Executive Officer
Felix Sulzberger.  The company is looking to open a new store in Lausanne,  Switzerland , Sulzberger told the newspaper.  For Related News and Information:
